in a crisscross star pattern (see Tip). Spread reserved thickened port syrup and figs in a circle over center of pastry and place Brie top-side down over figs. Fold pastry over cheese to cover. Trim excess pastry and press seams to seal. Place on prepared baking sheet seam-side down. Brush top and sides with whisked egg. Decorate with pastry scraps, brush decorations with remaining whisked egg and bake for 30-35 minutes (375°F), until puffed and golden brown. Garnish with fresh thyme leaves and serve hot with crackers and sliced apple."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Score the top rind so the cheese can get better exposure to heat. Use a small knife to make crisscross cuts in a star pattern or remove the top rind to expose the cheese."],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","1h 10m","2 portions"]}